                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>\n                <date>April 15. 1854</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear Friend — </p>\n            <p>I have recd the Books with Steamer<lb/> before last, and I hope by next time<lb/> to\n                be able to send you some money.<lb/> I have sold of the books thus far<lb/> 2 Bibles\n                at $9, 3 at $12—10 <persName>D.</persName> letters.<lb/> 2 German P. Books &amp; 1\n                set Prayer<lb/> Books at $31. I think you done wrong<lb/> incurring the expense of\n                sending<lb/> the books across the <placeName>Isthmus</placeName>, as people<lb/>\n                generally find it too much to pay<lb/> 50 cts. additional to every pound. I<lb/>\n                think I have written to you to make<lb/> a notice in the Occident that you have<lb/>\n                sent me out such books, which if you had<lb/> it done, would have assisted to\n                have<lb/> all the books sold till now; as there are<lb/> no doubt people which are\n                unaware that<lb/> I have these books to sell, who would want<lb/> them &amp; might\n                find it out through the Occident.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Now I will at once proceed to give you<lb/> some News; if I can\n                think or know<lb/> of any, as there are but very little of any interest</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p31n7z707/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
